Reviewed the refreshed shell for readability and contrast.

Confirmed the main readability protections remain intact:
- cream page surfaces keep long-form docs comfortable to read
- body text and headings use dark ink values with strong contrast
- inline code, preformatted blocks, nav links, and buttons retain clear separation from surrounding surfaces
- route colors are used as accents rather than replacing the primary reading colors

The visual refresh increases character without making the docs harder to scan.
